aoop.asteroids.model.game

Class ClientGame

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • aoop.asteroids.model.game.BaseGame
        • aoop.asteroids.model.game.ClientGame
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public final class ClientGame
extends BaseGame
implements java.lang.Runnable
    ClientGame is the representation of the game as it is seen on the Client-Side. This is rendered by AsteroidsPanel after each update step.
    ClientGame attempts to iterate the current game state by moving objects on their predicted paths, if no connection to the Server is currently available.
    This is repeated until a new GameUpdate packet arrives, and all internal lists of GameObjects are replaced with the up-to-date ones from the Server.
    Author:
    qqwy

      • setBackgroundImage

        public void setBackgroundImage(int index)
        The background-image is chosen from a list of `tscapeN.jpg` images, where N is in the range (0..7). The actual image used is dependent on the current round number. The used images are tiling (repeating) in both the horizontal and the vertical direction.

        index -
